  "event_preview": "Riverhead Raceway is a 0.250-mile (0.402 km) asphalt oval in Riverhead, New York, opened in 1951 with 12 degrees of banking in the turns and 6 degrees on the straights. The tight, high-banked quarter-mile creates an intense racing environment where track position and pit strategy are paramount. The Miller Lite Salutes Don Howe 200 is the fifth race of the 2026 NASCAR Whelen Modified Tour season and the 78th Whelen Modified Tour appearance at the historic bullring located on Long Island, run over 200 laps (50 miles). The race is held in honor of Don Howe, a five-time Riverhead Raceway Modified champion.\n\nJustin Bonsignore leads all competitors with 12 Whelen Modified Tour triumphs at Riverhead, and arrives seeking his 13th victory at the venue. In 31 career starts at Riverhead, Bonsignore has finished outside the top five on just five occasions and has led 1,740 laps with an average finish of 4.9. Other notable winners at Riverhead include Mike Ewanitsko, Jimmy Spencer, Reggie Ruggiero, Mike Stefanik, Donny Lia, Ryan Preece, Ted Christopher, Doug Coby and Steve Park. Stephen Kopcik leads the 2026 Whelen Modified Tour championship standings heading into the weekend.\n\nThe all-time Whelen Modified Tour qualifying lap record at Riverhead belongs to Justin Bonsignore, who turned an 11.431-second lap (78.733 mph) on May 15, 2021 — a mark that broke the previous record held by Chuck Steuer since 2000.",
